# Cosign public key — embedded in the CLI binary for self-update signature verification.
#
# REPLACE THIS PLACEHOLDER with the real public key before the first
# production release. Generation procedure (one-time, on a YubiKey):
#
#   cosign generate-key-pair --kms hashivault://talyxion-cli-signing
#   cosign public-key --key hashivault://talyxion-cli-signing > talyxion.pub
#
# The corresponding private key MUST NEVER touch a CI runner — it lives on
# the YubiKey + KMS, and CI authenticates via OIDC + ephemeral signing
# session.
#
# Until the real key is generated, ``talyxion update`` will skip signature
# verification (with a loud warning) but still enforces SHA-256.

-----BEGIN PUBLIC KEY-----
PLACEHOLDER_NOT_A_REAL_KEY_REPLACE_BEFORE_PRODUCTION_RELEASE
-----END PUBLIC KEY-----
